INSTALLATION GUIDE

1. Generate a configure script file using the autoconf command

   % autoconf

2. Some environmental variables such as LD_LIBRARY_PATH, JAVA_HOME,
   and CXX must be correctly set so as to use ROSE, Xerces, and Xalan.

3. Run the configure script

   % ./configure --prefix=/path/to/somewhere \
                 --with-rosedir=/usr/local/ \
                 --with-xercescdir=/usr/local \
                 --with-xalancdir=/usr/local

4. Run the GNU make command.

   To compile the package,

   % make

   To install the package,

   % make install

   To test the package,

   % make check
